                            <comment id="92991" author="rwinch" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2013 07:22:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since Java config has not had a stable release it is not necessary to be passive, so this is not a bug. In the future, questions about how to do something should be sent to the forums or stackoverflow with the spring-security tag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To see how to disable CSRF, please see &lt;a href=&quot;http://blog.springsource.org/2013/08/21/spring-security-3-2-0-rc1-highlights-csrf-protection/#configure-csrf-protection&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://blog.springsource.org/2013/08/21/spring-security-3-2-0-rc1-highlights-csrf-protection/#configure-csrf-protection&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS: Thanks for the heads upon the documentation (this was a bug). The link at &lt;a href=&quot;http://static.springsource.org/spring-security/site/reference.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://static.springsource.org/spring-security/site/reference.html&lt;/a&gt; was incorrect and has now been updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
